      <div xml:id="Aink4-kilavi">
        <p type="edition"> ituvumatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"> </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="Aink4">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> vāḻi yātaṉ vāḻi yaviṉi</l>
          <l> pakaivarpul lārka pārppā rōtuka</l>
          <l> veṉavēṭ ṭōḷē yāyē yāmē</l>
          <l> pūtta karumpiṟ kāytta nelliṟ</l>
          <l> kaḻaṉi yūraṉ mārpu </l>
          <l> paḻaṉamā kaṟka veṉavēṭ ṭēmē.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">

<l>          'Long live Ātan! Long live Aviṉi! </l>
<l>          May [our] enemies glut themselves on grass! May the Brahmins chant!' </l>
<l>          That's what our mother wants. As for us: </l>
<l>          'There is a man from a land of fields </l>
<l>          where the paddy has turned hard [like] ripe sugarcane: </l>
<l>          May [his] chest not become a public bath!' — that's what we want. </l>
          


        </lg>
      </div>
